  "serviceNotes": {
    "engine oil": "For VA-chassis WRX models, Subaru North American maintenance literature specifies frequent engine oil and filter changes for the turbocharged FA20F (commonly every 6,000 miles / 6 months under the standard schedule)\u2014approximately 10,000 km / 6 months; confirm in your warranty and maintenance booklet.",
    "cabin air filter": "Cabin/pollen filter replacement follows the periodic maintenance table in your Subaru warranty and maintenance booklet (typically on a 20,000\u201330,000 km / 12\u201324 month pattern depending on region).",
    "air cleaner element": "Engine air cleaner replacement is called out in Subaru maintenance schedules on a distance/time basis; 30,000 km / 24 months is a reasonable baseline where the booklet groups it with major services\u2014verify for your model year.",
    "spark plugs": "FA20F WRX maintenance booklets in North America commonly specify spark plug service around the 60,000-mile (~96,000 km) major service with a time cap in some markets\u2014always use the plug type and interval listed for your year.",
    "brake fluid": "Subaru of America documents periodic brake fluid replacement (often cited around 30 months with additional distance triggers in some booklets); this row is time-only (km null) per app schema\u2014see your official maintenance table.",
    "inspect disc brake pads": "Disc brake pad and rotor inspection is performed at each scheduled maintenance interval under Subaru\u2019s normal driving maintenance programme.",
    "front differential oil": "All-wheel-drive WRX models require front differential oil service; Subaru maintenance tables specify replacement at major intervals (commonly around 60,000 km / 48 months in global booklets for performance AWD models)\u2014confirm against your region\u2019s schedule.",
    "rear differential oil": "Rear differential oil is replaced on the same major-interval pattern as the front differential in Subaru WRX maintenance tables\u2014verify exact km/months in your booklet.",
    "intake carbon clean": "Direct injection without port washing can deposit intake-valve carbon; walnut or chemical cleaning around 120,000 km is a common specialist recommendation when cold-start misfire or rough idle appears.",
    "CVT fluid": "Subaru Lineartronic CVT models may list \u2018lifetime\u2019 fluid in some markets; many specialists recommend fluid service near 60,000 km for long-term reliability on performance-oriented use.",
    "manual transmission oil": "Factory schedules often inspect manual transmission oil; a preventive change near 120,000 km is a common recommendation when the fluid darkens or after hard use."
  },
